cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.MM

This paper deals with the problem of optimal content placement in a cellular network, which is a topic related to network optimization and information theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a sequential content update rule that converges to the optimal content placement, which involves distributed decision-making and control, suggesting that it could also be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper involves estimation of content popularities and cell topology, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper deals with caching, which could be classified under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
